     model="claude-haiku-4-5",
     max_tokens=1500,
     system=[{"type":"text","text": ONTOLOGY,
              "cache_control":{"type":"ephemeral"}}],
     messages=[{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text": MD_SLICE}]}]
 )

 Input scope: past 30 days of reports/*_news_digest.md, reports/*_sector_report.md, deep-dive MDs, postmortems. Strip frontmatter, window to 6k tokens per slice.

 Output schema (LLM must emit JSON):
 {"entities": [{"id":"theme:hbm_base_die_n3_pull_through","label":"...","type":"narrative"}],
  "triples":  [{"source":"ticker:NVDA","edge":"CATALYST_FOR",
                "target":"catalyst:GTC_2026","confidence":0.92}]}

 Idempotency + cost:
 - Cache key = sha256(md_path + mtime_ns). Cached MDs skip API. Re-running same day costs $0.
 - Daily steady-state budget: ~40 MDs × ~3k tokens × system-prompt cache hit → ~$0.05/day.
 - First-run backfill containment (Gemini risk #2): on first invocation, 30 days × ~40 reports/day × ~3k tokens ≈ 3.6M input tokens. To avoid first-day cost spike:
   - --backfill-limit N flag (default 10 reports/run) — backfill spread over ~30 days
   - OR --backfill-since DATE to bound the window
   - Worst case full backfill at Haiku 4.5 rates: ≈$3 one-time, still bounded
 - Canonicalize labels via re.sub(r"\W+","_", lower()) + alias map in config.yaml.

 Alias canonicalization guard (per Gemini enhancement #2, mandatory two-stage post-process):

 Stage 1 — Hard canonicalization against existing project sources:
 1. Load skills/_shared/industry_name_mapping.yaml (if exists) + Dashboard/heatmap_universe.json (517 tickers) + skills/_shared/company_context.py SECTOR_UNIVERSE
 2. Any LLM-emitted entity matching by alias (case-insensitive, fuzzy rapidfuzz.ratio > 90) → forced canonical id (e.g., "Taiwan Semi" / "TSMC" / "台積電" → ticker:TSM)
 3. Build alias map cache at scripts/nexus/cache/alias_resolved.json for hit-replay

 Stage 2 — Provisional vs. promoted classification:
 - LLM emits an entity that does NOT match any known ticker / theme / sector
 → default to type: narrative (NOT ticker)
 → marked status: provisional
 - Entity only "promoted" to first-class node (e.g., narrative → recognized theme, or recognized as ticker candidate) after appearing in ≥3 independent source documents (different MD paths, not same-day
 duplicates)
 - Provisional nodes still render but with reduced visual weight + warning hover badge

 Rejected triples (failed Stage 1 ticker whitelist) → scripts/nexus/cache/rejected.jsonl for manual review.

