 Top 4 Risks + Mitigations

 1. Tier 3 LLM hallucinates / fragments nodes (Taiwan Semi vs TSM vs TSMC as separate nodes) → graph noise + misleading centrality.
   - Mitigation: two-stage canonicalization in Phase C (hard alias + ≥3-doc promotion rule). All Tier 3 entities default to provisional narrative type until proven. Rejected →
 scripts/nexus/cache/rejected.jsonl.
 2. nexus_graph.json balloons past 5MB → frontend force-graph stalls / browser hangs (Gemini risk #1).
   - Mitigation: pruning pipeline in build_graph.py AFTER decay AND BEFORE centrality:
       - Drop isolated leaf nodes (degree 1 AND final_weight < 0.05)
     - Drop provisional narratives with mention_count < 3
     - Sort remaining edges by final_weight desc, hard cap at max_nodes: 800
     - assert len(json.dumps(graph)) < 5_000_000 before write
   - Output ledger: log dropped-node + dropped-edge counts to scripts/nexus/cache/build_log_<DATE>.json for audit.
 3. First-day LLM cost spike on 30-day backfill (Gemini risk #2).
   - Mitigation: --backfill-limit 10 flag (default); SHA256 cache makes each MD a one-time cost; spread backfill across ~30 days of daily runs. Worst case full backfill ≈$3 one-time.
 4. networkx not installed in current env (Gemini diagnostic).
   - Mitigation: triple fallback — networkx → pagerank_lite.py (Power Iteration, ~20 lines, no deps) → degree-only. daily_update.sh attempts pip install networkx --quiet once; if fails, fallback engages
 silently. Step 7 non-fatal.

